CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 23, 1952, pg. 12, reads: "Newlyweds - Mr. and Mrs. Elmer Jennings, 206 Carver Street, East Liberty, announce the recent marriage of their daughter, Marie, to Edward Vaughn. Attending the bride were Mary Jennings and Dora Jean Pinkett. The groom is the son of Mr. and Mrs. Edward Vaughn. His brother, Donald Vaughn, was best man for the occasion. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom Edward Vaughn and bride Marie Jennings cutting three tiered wedding cake, possibly in Jennings home, 206 Carver Street, East Liberty
